---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Young Adults"
  description="Concerned about a young adult's gambling? How to recognize the signs and start the conversation — for parents, partners, siblings, and friends."
>
  <header class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="page-header__eyebrow">
        <a href="/family-and-friends">← Family &amp; friends</a>
      </p>
      <h1>Young Adults</h1>
      <p class="page-header__lead">
        Concerned about a young adult's gambling? Here's how to recognize the
        signs and open a real conversation that doesn't close again.
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="fnf-top">
    <div class="container fnf-top__grid">
      <div class="fnf-top__main">
        <p>
          For young adults today, gambling often starts on a phone. Sports-
          betting apps, prediction markets, fantasy contests, and crypto-style
          trading platforms that feel a lot like betting share the same
          notification stream as the rest of their life. The line between "a
          hobby" and "a problem" can blur fast — and the line between
          independence and harm is what's hardest for the people around them to
          read.
        </p>
        <p>
          You don't need to be a clinician to help. The most powerful thing you
          can do is open a real conversation — and not let it close again.
        </p>
      </div>
      <aside class="fnf-top__aside">
        <figure class="fnf-photo">
          <img
            src="/photos/family-and-friends/young-adults.jpg"
            alt="Two adults in close, thoughtful conversation indoors."
            width="800"
            height="600"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </figure>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <p>
        More detailed guidance — signs to watch for, how to start the
        conversation, what not to do, and how to take care of yourself — is
        being developed for this page. The same framework as the
        <a href="/family-and-friends/youth">Youth</a> page applies; the
        cohort-specific adaptation is in progress.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
